===Etymology===
From {{L.|pt}} '''[[sto#Latin|stō]]''', "[[stand]]"

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/esˈtaɾ/}}, {{IPA|/isˈtaɾ/}}, {{IPA|/iʃˈtaɾ/}}

===Verb===
{{pt-verb-ar|stem=est|first singular=estou|third plural|estão}}

# Indicates location in space; to [[be]];
#: "''Onde '''estás'''?''" - Where are you?
#: "'''''Estou''' em casa''" - I am at home
# Denotes a transient quality; to [[be]], to [[stay]];
#: "''O tempo '''estava''' frio''" - The weather was cold (at that moment).
#: "'''''Estás''' louco?''" - Are you crazy (right now)?
# Auxiliary verb for the progressive tense, precedes verb in gerund; to [[be]].
#: "''Ela '''está''' cantando?''" - Is she singing?
#: "''Nos últimos dias, eles '''estão''' trabalhando muito." - Last days, they are working a lot.

